---
import Button from "./Button.astro";
---

<div class="learningStylesPage">
    <h1 class="learningText"> Various Learning Styles </h1>
    <div class="readings">
        <h1 class="readingsText"> Readings </h1>
        <div class="box">
            <div class="rect"></div>
            <div class="quickSortExample">
                <div class="quickSort">
                    <h1 class="quickSortText"> Quick Sort </h1>
                    <p1> Quicksort works by partitioning an array based on an arbitrary element in the array, which we will refer to as p. The array is divided into two subarrays, one which contains elements larger than p, and one which contains elements smaller than p. The operation is then repeated with each of the subarrays, with a new p for each subarray, until the array is separated into sub-arrays with a designated length, usually 1. p is also known as the pivot. </p1>    
                </div>
                <Button title="Read More" link="/Markdown/quicksort" color="#EB3933" shadow="#BA1812" highlight="#BA1812"/>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="videos">
        <h1 class="videosText"> Videos </h1>
        <div class="video">
            <iframe src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Q9Rul23upNs-mhCig4BZJm7qLsb5MTGZ/preview" />
            <div class="videoSide">
                <Button title="Watch" link="/" color="#5CC6FF" shadow="#0077B8" highlight="#0077B8"/>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="weirdblob">
        <img src="/images/weirdBlob.svg">
    </div>

    <div class="practiceExercises">
        <h1 class="practiceExerciseText"> Practice Exercises </h1>
        <div class="practiceExercise">
            <div class="exercise">
                <p1>
                    When would QuickSort take O(n<sup>2</sup>) time to sort?
                </p1>
                <Button title="Try it" link="/Markdown/quicksort" color="#0077B8" shadow="#005D8F" highlight="#005D8F"/>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise">
                <p1>
                    Why do we use decision trees to model binary search?
                </p1>
                <Button title="Try it" link="/Markdown/binary-search-trees" color="#0077B8" shadow="#005D8F" highlight="#005D8F"/>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise">
                <p1>
                    Do queues handle multiple data types?
                </p1>
                <Button title="Try it" link="/Markdown/queues" color="#0077B8" shadow="#005D8F" highlight="#005D8F"/>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:ital,wght@0,100;0,300;0,400;0,700;0,900;1,100;1,300;1,400;1,700;1,900&display=swap');
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800&display=swap');

    .learningStylesPage {
        display: grid;
        grid-auto-rows: minmax(min-content, max-content);
        overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .learningText {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        font-family: "Lato";
        font-weight: 900;
        font-size: 5rem;
        padding-top: 4rem;
        grid-column: 1;
        grid-row: 1;
    }

    .readings {
        grid-column: 1;
        grid-row: 2;
    }

    .videos {
        grid-column: 1;
        grid-row: 3;
    }

    .readings, .videos, .practiceExercises {
        margin-inline: 6.25rem;
    }

    .readings h1, .videos h1, .practiceExercises h1 {
        font-family: "Lato";
        margin: 0rem;
    }

    .readings p1, .videos p1 {
        font-family: 'Open Sans';
    }

    .readingsText, .videosText, .practiceExerciseText {
        font-weight: 900;
        color: #EB3933;
        font-size: 4rem;
        padding-bottom: 1rem;
        padding-top: 4rem;
    }

    .box {
        width: auto;
    }

    .rect {
        background: #5CC6FF;
        height: 3.5rem;
        border: 2px solid black;
    }

    .quickSortExample {
        display: flex;
        border-inline: 2px solid black;
        border-bottom: 2px solid black;
        padding: 2rem;
        background-color: white;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .quickSortText {
        padding-bottom: 0.2rem;
    }

    .quickSort {
        width: 60vw;
    }

    .videos iframe {
        width: 65vw;
        height: 65vh;
    }

    .video {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
    }

    .videos p1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .videoSide {
        inline-size: 20rem;
        overflow-wrap: break-word;
        text-align: center;
        display: grid;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-left: 5.55vw;
        gap: 4rem;
    }

    .videoSide p1 {
        grid-column: 1;
        grid-row: 1;
    }

    .weirdblob {
        grid-column: 1;
        grid-row: 2;
        z-index: -1;
    }

    .practiceExercises {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .exercise {
        background: #f2f2f2;
        padding: 2rem;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin: 1rem;
    }

    .exercise p1 {
        font-family: "Open Sans";
        font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

</style>